  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1941",
  "title": "Custom Widgets",
  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nFeature\r\n\r\n**Feature: What is your use case for such a feature?**\r\nExample, I want to create a menu for `State` facet, I have to do these steps:\r\n```js\r\n// create a custom menu\r\nconst MenuContainer = connectMenu(Menu)\r\n\r\n// then use it as\r\n<MenuContainer attributeName=\"state\" />\r\n```\r\nWhen I need to create a custom widget, I could only use this widget for a specified facet, not for all facets. It means `Menu` component is how to display my State facet (it should be named `StateMenu`)\r\nNotice: that there are a repeat step `attributeName=\"state\"`.\r\n\r\n**Feature: What is your proposed API entry? The new option to add? What is the behavior?**\r\nIt's great if providing an API option like this:\r\n```js\r\n// create a custom menu\r\nconst StateMenuContainer = connectMenu(StateMenu, { attributeName: 'state' })\r\n\r\n// then use it as\r\n<StateMenuContainer/>\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
